Hall of Fame Catcher Gary Carter Has Four Brain Tumors

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-05-21T20:28:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-21/hall-of-fame-catcher-gary-carter-has-four-brain-tumors.html
New York Mets Hall of Fame catcher
Gary Carter has been diagnosed with four “very small” tumors
on his brain.  Carter, 57, said he underwent an MRI yesterday in  West Palm
Beach , Florida, which revealed the tumors.  “I am scheduled to be examined further Thursday at Duke
Medical Center and we will learn more at that time about my
diagnosis,” Carter said in a statement released through the
Mets.  Over 19 seasons in Major League Baseball with the Montreal
Expos, Mets, San Francisco Giants and  Los Angeles Dodgers ,
Carter batted .262 with 324 home runs and 1,225 runs batted in.
An 11-time All-Star, he helped the Mets to the 1986 World Series
title and was elected to the Baseball Hall of Fame in 2003.  He spent the past two seasons as  baseball coach  at Palm
Beach Atlantic College in  Florida .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bob Bensch in London at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Elser at   celser@bloomberg.net . 